The paper deals with efficient exploration in Reinforcement Learning, which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of forward models and optimization techniques to plan for novel events falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the scalability of the algorithm to high-dimensional continuous environments, which could be related to Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
